1. Open the Common Canvas side panel (click the hamburger icon)
2. Select the `Explain` sample application

You will see the nodes have different shapes and colors based on their type. You can examine the <a href="https://github.com/elyra-ai/canvas/blob/master/canvas_modules/harness/src/client/components/custom-canvases/explain/explain-canvas.jsx">Explain sample app code</a> to see how it works. This involves these three parts:

1. <a href="https://github.com/elyra-ai/canvas/blob/3e2a1be61047b6ea85fe13020a00ec5dc8a41405/canvas_modules/harness/src/client/components/custom-canvases/explain/explain-canvas.jsx#L15">This line</a> sets the `enableConnectionType` which will set all nodeLayout properties to their defaults.
2. <a href="https://github.com/elyra-ai/canvas/blob/3e2a1be61047b6ea85fe13020a00ec5dc8a41405/canvas_modules/harness/src/client/components/custom-canvases/explain/explain-canvas.jsx#L17">This line</a> will override the node layout defaults with ones specified for all nodes.
3. <a href="https://github.com/elyra-ai/canvas/blob/3e2a1be61047b6ea85fe13020a00ec5dc8a41405/canvas_modules/harness/src/client/components/custom-canvases/explain/explain-canvas.jsx#L39">The layout handler</a> will override layout properties on a node by node basis.
